  `src/evalforge/migrations/**`, `docs/operations.md`, and a future user-selected Git remote.
- **When:** After the user authorizes a publication destination or before claiming external CI or
  PostgreSQL validation.
- **Detailed description:** Configuration and contract tests validate the optional
  `postgresql+psycopg` path. Only a real service-backed run proves runner networking, packaged
  migration behavior, browser availability, and service readiness.
- **Acceptance criteria:**
  - A remote Actions run is green for Ruff, mypy, Bandit, pip-audit, deterministic coverage,
    PostgreSQL migration/seed/doctor, package build, and Playwright E2E.
  - PostgreSQL reaches the packaged migration head, seeds deterministic fixtures, reports ready, and
    leaves no unexpected schema diff.
  - The immutable run URL, commit SHA, and relevant logs are recorded without secrets.
- **Definition of done:** Configure a user-selected remote, push the local commits, execute CI,
  remediate runner-only failures, protect required jobs, and update the completion record with exact
  external evidence.
- **Reason the issue exists:** The user requested a new local project and did not provide authority
  or a destination for remote publication.
- **Priority:** P3.
- **Why this priority:** The required SQLite path is deeply proven; PostgreSQL and remote CI are
  optional external proof layers.
- **How to prevent regressions:** Required protected jobs, migration/schema-diff tests, explicit
  driver validation, service readiness checks, and retained run links.
- **How to test:** Pytest integration against the CI PostgreSQL service and Playwright E2E in a
  separate CI job.
- **Audit policies:** Validation-proof selection, state-readback persistence, route/API contract
  mapping, preexisting-failure triage, and deploy-automation hazards.
- **Other considerations:**
  - Keep credentials in CI secrets and out of logs/artifacts.
  - Do not broaden deployment scope merely because a remote exists.
  - Horizontal workers still require the separate durable-queue item.

## P3 — Calibrate paid-provider and optional judge integrations before release gating

- **Who:** EvalForge evaluation methodology and provider owner.
- **What:** OpenAI-compatible provider contracts are mocked, but no paid live call, human threshold
  calibration, RAGAS/DeepEval plugin, LLM judge, LangSmith exporter, or W&B exporter was executed.
- **How discovered:** Provider/metric/docs review, the user's optional stack list, and the explicit
  no-paid-call proof boundary used throughout Phase 2.
- **Where:** `src/evalforge/evaluation/adapters/openai_compatible.py`,
  `src/evalforge/evaluation/metrics.py`, immutable run/export schemas, Settings and preflight UI,
  and evaluation-methodology/security documentation.
- **When:** Before enabling external providers in a shared environment or using heuristic/judge
  scores as production release gates.
- **Detailed description:** The deterministic lexical and evidence metrics are transparent
  regression signals, not factual truth. Any external judge or tracker must preserve model, endpoint
  mode, rubric bytes/hash, schema, version, calibration set, applicability, request ID, usage, cost,
  and privacy scope without replacing or weakening offline operation.
- **Acceptance criteria:**
  - A small explicitly authorized live run preserves request IDs, usage, latency, pricing source,
    and sanitized provider errors without leaking secrets.
  - Human-reviewed calibration reports agreement, precision/recall, or another declared measure at
    the selected thresholds.
  - Judge/plugin results are versioned, explainable, and not-applicable when prerequisites are
    missing.
  - Paid execution retains conservative preflight, explicit confirmation, spend caps, and
    offline-by-default CI.
- **Definition of done:** Implement any selected optional adapter/exporter behind a provider-neutral
  interface, add mocked contract tests, perform a bounded authorized live proof, write a calibration
  artifact, and document exact privacy and accuracy limitations.
- **Reason the issue exists:** Live spend and external data transmission require credentials and
  explicit authority. Optional evaluator/tracking services were not required for the complete
  offline product.
- **Priority:** P3 for calibration before gating; exporter-only work is P4.
- **Why this priority:** It improves external validity and observability rather than repairing local
  Phase 2 correctness.
- **How to prevent regressions:** Marked live tests, offline-by-default CI, immutable rubric/provider
  versions, cost caps, calibration-set versioning, and no silent provider fallback.
- **How to test:** Mocked unit/integration contracts by default; explicitly marked bounded live tests;
  human calibration review; Playwright for disclosure, consent, and pricing-state UI.
- **Audit policies:** Payment/cost safety, security/privacy review, route/API contract mapping,
  state-readback persistence, and validation-proof selection.
- **Other considerations:**
  - Never pass references into candidate prompts.
  - Never report unknown cost as zero or synthetic telemetry as live.
  - Never silently fall back between provider API modes.
  - Keep LangSmith/W&B export optional and secret-safe.

