# 7. Established Processes & Effective Patterns

**Freshness: ✅ High — recently verified in this session.**

1. Read the newest repo handoff before discovery.
2. Use the secret-safe wrapper for every terminal command; use URL-safe base64 argv for shell
   metacharacters, environment assignment, or complex arguments.
3. Write a concrete plan before multi-surface implementation.
4. Add a failing behavior/contract test, implement the minimum truthful behavior, then refactor.
5. Keep API analytics bounded to completed persisted evidence with explicit denominators.
6. For UI changes, inspect the source and rendered page; source review alone is insufficient.
7. Browser workflow: snapshot -> unique locator count -> interaction -> fresh snapshot -> screenshot
   and logs -> overflow check.
8. Restart the owned Streamlit process after module edits when the file watcher is unavailable, then
   open a clean tab for final evidence.
9. Separate deterministic/local/browser/E2E/hosted/provider/production proof layers.
10. Run focused tests, full branch coverage, Ruff, mypy, Bandit, pip-audit, frozen sync, Playwright,
    and whitespace checks.
11. Stage exact files, commit locally, then write completion and handoff docs with the implementation
    SHA.
12. Stop only owned runtimes and verify their ports are clear.

